From: bb-epaper firmware
Subject: [PATCH] GxEPD2_750_GDEY075T7: bump full_refresh_time 1200 -> 5000 ms

The stock value (1200 ms) is calibrated for the fast/partial-style refresh.
When the BUSY pin is not connected (BUSY=-1 at construction), GxEPD2's
`_waitWhileBusy` falls back to `delay(busy_time)`, so `full_refresh_time`
becomes load-bearing for full updates. A real 7.5" UC8179 full refresh
takes ~4.1 s; with 1200 ms, the driver calls `powerOff()` mid-scan and
only the top ~8% of the panel commits.

Apply to your local GxEPD2 install:

    cd ~/Arduino/libraries/GxEPD2
    patch -p1 < /usr/local/bb-epaper/firmware/patches/GxEPD2_750_GDEY075T7-full_refresh_time.patch

Drop this patch (revert to 1200) if/when BUSY is wired correctly on the
Seeed XIAO ePaper Display Board EE04/EE05 carrier — once BUSY can be
polled, `full_refresh_time` is no longer load-bearing.

--- a/src/gdey/GxEPD2_750_GDEY075T7.h
+++ b/src/gdey/GxEPD2_750_GDEY075T7.h
@@ -32,7 +32,7 @@ class GxEPD2_750_GDEY075T7 : public GxEPD2_EPD
     static const bool useFastPartialUpdateFromOTP = true; // set this false for earlier batches, such as the panel I have (1580258us)
     static const uint16_t power_on_time = 140; // ms, e.g. 129018us
     static const uint16_t power_off_time = 42; // ms, e.g. 40430us
-    static const uint16_t full_refresh_time = 1200; // ms, e.g. 1171000us
+    static const uint16_t full_refresh_time = 5000; // ms — bumped from 1200 for BUSY=-1 fallback on bb-epaper (real UC8179 scan ~4.1s)
     static const uint16_t partial_refresh_time = 450; // ms, e.g. 435000us
     // constructor
     GxEPD2_750_GDEY075T7(int16_t cs, int16_t dc, int16_t rst, int16_t busy);
